<html>
  <head>
    <title>About Travlr Getaways</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="page">
      <header class="header">
        <div class="header__title">About Travlr Getaways</div>
        <div class="header__sub">Who we are and how this app is built.</div>
        <div class="header__actions">
          <a class="btn btn-light" href="/">Home</a>
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/trips">Browse Trips</a>
        </div>
      </header>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="about-grid">
          <div class="about-grid__left">
            <div class="card">
              <div class="card__body">
                <h3 class="card__title">Our Mission</h3>
                <p class="card__text">Travlr Getaways keeps trip info simple and
                  transparent. Clear pricing, real dates, and a clean interface
                  so travelers can decide fast.</p>
                <p class="card__text">This app is built with the MEAN stack:
                  Angular for the admin front end, Express and Node for the API,
                  and MongoDB for the database. The customer pages are
                  server-rendered with Handlebars for fast first paint.</p>
                <p class="card__text">Recent enhancements include
                  environment-based configuration, security headers with Helmet,
                  a global error handler, and a refreshed responsive design for
                  an easier browsing experience.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="about-grid__right">
            <div class="card">
              <div class="card__media card__media--ratio">
                <img
                  src="/travlr-getaways/public/images/logo2.png"
                  alt="logo"
                />
              </div>
              <div class="card__body">
                <h3 class="card__title">Tech Snapshot</h3>
                <ul class="list">
                  <li>Node.js + Express API</li>
                  <li>MongoDB with Mongoose</li>
                  <li>Handlebars SSR for customer pages</li>
                  <li>Angular admin (localhost:4200)</li>
                  <li>Helmet, CORS, dotenv, global error handler</li>
                </ul>
                <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/trips">See trips</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>